INCENTIVIZE.Definition: motivate or encourage someone to do something

DISCOURAGED.Definition: having lost your confidence or enthusiasm for something

MODERATELY.Definition: something that is average or within reasonable limits

REMAIN.Definition: to stay in the same place or in the same condition

HIDDEN.Definition: kept out of sight; difficult to see or find

AMBUSH.Definition: to attack someone by surprise from a hidden place

PREY.Definition: an animal that is hunted and killed for food by another animal

LACK OF.Definition: the state of being without or not having enough of something

CONTENT.Definition: state of being satisfied; not wanting more or anything else

JERSEYS.Definition: a shirt worn by a member of a sports team as part of a uniform

ENVIRONMENT.Definition: the surroundings or conditions in which a person lives or operates
